{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17621320","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17621320"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T15:52:26+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T15:52:26+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16691"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16691","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16691"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[1,0,0,0,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9382"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66942"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9382","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9382"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16691"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52396"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"9"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"1643"},{"type":"tags","id":"2982"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"5326"},{"type":"tags","id":"5423"},{"type":"tags","id":"9623"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22200"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22385"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66942","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/66942"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA two-year-old child presents to the Emergency Department with multiple bruises. The parent reports the child fell while playing in the garden yesterday.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EPhysical examination reveals:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003EMultiple bruises of different colours on the back and buttocks\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003ECircular bruises on both upper arms\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003ELinear marks across the lower back\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EChild appears withdrawn and fearful\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the most appropriate initial action?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Document findings and notify child protection services","Refer to general practitioner for follow-up","Prescribe analgesia and review in one week","Order skeletal survey only","Discharge home with safety advice"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe most appropriate action is to \u003Cstrong\u003Edocument findings and notify child protection services\u003C/strong\u003E. The pattern of injuries is inconsistent with the reported mechanism and suggests non-accidental injury. Multiple bruises of different ages and bruising in protected areas (back, buttocks) are concerning features.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options are inappropriate because:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDischarge home with safety advice\u003C/strong\u003E would place the child at risk of further harm.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOrder skeletal survey only\u003C/strong\u003E delays appropriate intervention and reporting.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPrescribe analgesia and review in one week\u003C/strong\u003E fails to address immediate safety concerns.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERefer to general practitioner for follow-up\u003C/strong\u003E does not provide immediate protection for the child.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHealthcare providers have a mandatory obligation to report suspected child abuse. Documentation should be thorough and objective, including photographs where possible. The child\u0027s safety is the primary concern.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Non-accidental injury in children commonly presents with injuries inconsistent with the reported mechanism or developmental stage.","Bruising patterns that suggest non-accidental injury include multiple bruises of different ages and bruises in protected areas.","Healthcare providers have a legal obligation to report suspected cases of child abuse to child protection services."],"references":["Smith A. Nonaccidental injury in childhood. Aust Fam Physician. 2011;40(11):858-861. Available from: https://www.racgp.org.au/getattachment/5cbf2ff1-a135-43e1-8dbd-837743bb29bf/Nonaccidental-injury-in-childhood.aspx","Royal Children\u0027s Hospital. Child Abuse. Updated November 2021. Available from: https://www.rch.org.au/clinicalguide/guideline_index/Child_abuse/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52396"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16691"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52396","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/52396"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-03T08:27:01+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-03T08:28:21+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9382"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66942"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"9","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/9"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc76","name":"Paediatrics","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-01-16T08:39:03+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"24","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/24"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude91","name":"Emergency Medicine","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":nu